sm and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":88,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":99,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":101,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Loggesden was born about 1470, in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, his father, John Loggesden, was 31 and his mother, Eliza Ann Pattinson, was 31. He married Mary before 1500, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1470–":"umbes 1470–Surnud","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1465–Female":"1465–Surnud","1502–1553":"1502–1553","1440–1480":"1440–1480","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","about 1470":"umbes 1470","before 1500":"enne 1500","1440":"1440","1571":"1571","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1502":"1502","1553":"1553","1465":"1465","about 1502":"umbes 1502","1549":"1549","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northampton